snippet.title: Computer Science YouTuber Makes This Surprising Program for Subscribers...
snippet.description:
Looking for vids from a Computer Science YouTuber?  You've come to the right place :)

💻 I have changed my website since this video. But you can still visit at alexlorenlee.com

If you're new to this channel I make Java tutorials every week to help beginners to computer science learn how to code. If you want to see all my videos as soon as they come out you can click the subscribe button and the bell next to it.

Seeing people's reactions is what drives me to do computer science. A smile, a laugh or an insight is my goal when writing a program for someone. It's what inspires me to continue adding to this beginner software engineering channel. I hope you liked this :)

This project took 2 weeks. I created an automated web browser tool to get the images of my public subscriber's channels (you). Next I stored them in a database and put you up on the website with some cool javascript physics library!

This is what I live for and I really want to thank you all again! 

Stay tuned for the 500 subscribers video... ;)

I work as a Test Enginner but yes, I consider myself a Software Engineer YouTuber / Computer Science YouTuber :) -

Free tips and programs: http://alexlorenlee.com

Recommended Channels to Subscribe to

TheNewBoston: https://youtube.com/user/thenewboston

~

Alex Lee
